    <text id="R14696170T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>John C. Babcock writes Union General George Meade in January, 1865, with
                    information regarding Confederate troop locations and organization. He reports
                    that General Jubal Early is in Staunton with his command.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Maj. Gen. GEORGE G. MEADE,<lb/> Cmdg. Army of the
                        Potomac:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-01-18">JANUARY 18, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>The following is the organization (present) of Early's old corps: Gordon
                    commanding corps; Battle's division (Rhode's old); Pegram's division (Early's
                    old); Grimes' division (Gordon's old). These three divisions compromise entire
                    remnants of Ewell's old corps. Early is at Staunton with a small command. Loss
                    of Fort Fisher not considered by the rebel press as of any particular
                    importance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>JNO. C. BABCOCK.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
